# Landing Page Playbook  > **Purpose**: Systematic process for creating high-converting landing pages > **Time Saved**: 2-4 hours per page (vs 6+ hours without workflow) > **When to Use**: Creating new landing pages, optimizing existing pages, A/B testing  ## The Growth Skills Workflow  The optimal sequence for landing page creation:  1. **`offer-coach`** → Define the transformation and value prop 2. **`landing-page-architect`** → Structure and conversion strategy 3. **`frontend-developer`** → Implementation 4. **`landing-page-optimization`** → Fine-tuning 5. **Quality checks** → ui-qa, web-accessibility, content-qa, seo-optimization  ---  ## Phase 1: Strategy & Offer Development (30 min)  ### 1.1 Define the Transformation  - [ ] **Use `offer-coach` skill** to clarify:   - What transformation are we promising?   - Who is the specific audience?   - What pain points do we solve?   - What outcomes do we deliver?  ### 1.2 Target Keyword Research  - [ ] **Use `seo-optimization` skill** for:   - Primary keyword (search volume, difficulty)   - Secondary keywords   - Competitor analysis   - Search intent validation

### 1.3 Value Proposition  - [ ] Write transformation statement:   ```   "From [current state] to [desired state] in [timeframe]   without [common objection/pain]"   ``` - [ ] List 3-5 key benefits (outcomes, not features) - [ ] Identify unique differentiator  ### 1.4 Success Metrics  - [ ] Define conversion goal (signup, trial, demo) - [ ] Set target conversion rate - [ ] Identify tracking events  ---  ## Phase 2: Page Architecture & Schema Planning (45 min)  ### 2.1 Schema Strategy (CRITICAL for SEO/AEO)  #### Determine Schema Types  - [ ] **Use `seo-optimization` skill** to determine which schemas apply:   - **Article** - Educational content, blog-style pages   - **FAQPage** - Pages with Q&A sections   - **HowTo** - Step-by-step guides   - **Product** - Product landing pages   - **Service** - Service offerings   - **LocalBusiness** - Location-based services   - **Course** - Educational programs   - **Event** - Webinars, workshops   - **Organization** - About/company pages   - **BreadcrumbList** - Navigation structure  #### Schema Selection Guide  ```markdown Content Type → Recommended Schemas ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ Educational landing → Article + FAQPage + BreadcrumbList Product landing → Product + FAQPage + Review Service landing → Service + FAQPage + LocalBusiness (if applicable) How-to guide → HowTo + FAQPage + Article Course/Program → Course + FAQPage + Organization Comparison page → Article + FAQPage + Product (multiple) ```  #### Implementation Checklist  - [ ] **Primary schema** (main content type) - [ ] **Supporting schemas** (FAQs, breadcrumbs) - [ ] **Rich snippets potential** (stars, prices, availability) - [ ] **Voice search optimization** (FAQ schema crucial)  ### 2.2 Structure Planning  - [ ] **Use `landing-page-architect` skill** for:   - Hero section hook   - Problem agitation   - Solution presentation   - Social proof placement   - CTA strategy   - **Schema-friendly content structure**
